In a press statement, the premier said that she “wishes to re-iterate the fact that the allegations outlined in the publication are entirely baseless and are not informed by facts”. Mtshweni-Tsipane confirmed that she is in good health, “and remains committed to ensuring that Mpumalanga enforces compliance with regulations aimed at flattening the curve of Covid-19 infections”. ALSO READ: Mopani Pharmacy under investigation for price gouging